921 et seq. The poet has laid down the fundamental principles of his own system, and shown the inadequacy of those adopted by others, Before proceeding to expound his doctrine in detail, he gives the poetic spirit play in this noble passage, which forms a graceful and appropriate transition from the general to the special portions of his subject.
